s/2016/04/Compatible-multipurpose-themes.png 568w" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /></p>\n<p>Today we are happy to announce a few¬†WPML compatible¬†Multipurpose Themes.</p>\n<p>The themes¬† are,¬†<a href="http://styledthemes.com/flat-responsive-pro">Flat Responsive Pro</a>, <a href="http://styledthemes.com/pure-simple">Pure &amp; Simple Pro</a>, <a href="http://styledthemes.com/lavish-pro">Lavish Pro</a>, <a href="http://themeforest.net/item/joyn-creative-multipurpose-theme/8854021">Joyn</a></p>\n<p>If you want to review the entire multilingual ready list of themes and plugins you are welcome to view it here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/">Multilingual Ready Themes</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/plugins-compatibility/">Multilingual Ready Plugins</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Also, if you‚Äôre a theme or a plugin author and you want to make it compatible with WPML, we welcome you and ready to help: You are welcome to contact us at <a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/theme-compatibility/go-global-program/">go global program page</a>.</p>\n<p>In order to expedite the process we strongly recommend that you test your theme or plugin with our¬†<a href="https://wpml.org/documentation/support/achieving-wpml-compatibility-for-your-themes-and-plugins/">Achieving WPML compatibility for your themes and plugins</a>. It easily tests compatibility with WPML and helps you quickly make your theme or plugin Multilingual Ready.</p>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Flat Responsive Pro</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Flat Responsive Pro is suitable for business websites.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="http://styledthemes.com/flat-responsive-pro">Purchase Flat Responsive Pro</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Lavish Pro</h2>\n<blockquote><p>A multi purpose theme with great features for blogging.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="http://styledthemes.com/lavish-pro">Purchase Lavish Pro</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Pure &amp; Simple Pro</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Pure and Simple is a responsive theme built for blogging.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="http://styledthemes.com/pure-simple">Purchase Pure &amp; Simple Pro</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feature">\n<h2 style="text-align: center;">Joyn</h2>\n<blockquote><p>Creative Multi-Purpose Theme.</p></blockquote>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="button download-button vt-p" href="http://themeforest.net/item/joyn-creative-multipurpose-theme/8854021">Purchase Joyn</a></p>\n</div>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=ZPPebCGnZ8I:6DSRSfiU5c0:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=ZPPebCGnZ8I:6DSRSfiU5c0:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=ZPPebCGnZ8I:6DSRSfiU5c0:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=ZPPebCGnZ8I:6DSRSfiU5c0:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=ZPPebCGnZ8I:6DSRSfiU5c0:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=ZPPebCGnZ8I:6DSRSfiU5c0:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/ZPPebCGnZ8I" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:71:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/compatible-multipurposethemes-april-2016/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:66:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/compatible-multipurposethemes-april-2016/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:54:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"How to use WPML with different domains per language";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/Pv7Xg6vCv-s/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:73:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/use-wpml-different-domains-per-language/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 22 Apr 2016 13:55:50 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Tutorials";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"dns";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"domain";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"http";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"subdomain";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"https://wpml.org/?p=860077";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:311:"So, you want to have a WPML site with the different domain per language option? There are some nice advantages of using different domains in your site that go well beyond appearances. Some people prefer to access a domain name that looks to belong to their own country and this can create a loyalty in [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"George Botsev";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:15717:"<p>So, you want to have a WPML site with the different domain per language option?<br />\nThere are some nice advantages of using different domains in your site that go well beyond appearances.</p>\n<p>Some people prefer to access a domain name that looks to belong to their own country and this can create a loyalty in your visitors. There is a kind of SEO bonus as well, because you can use the domains to better target your users.</p>\n<div id="attachment_860383" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/languages.png"><img class="wp-image-860383 size-medium" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/languages-300x187.png" alt="Different domains per language are setup on the WPML -&gt; Languages page." width="300" height="187" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/languages-300x187.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/languages-150x94.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/languages-768x480.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/languages-1024x640.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/languages.png 1397w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Different domains per language are setup on the WPML -&gt; Languages page.</p></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>First, let&#8217;s explain what this exactly means when used in practice.</p>\n<p>If for example, you want to have English and German languages with WPML and different domain per language option.</p>\n<p>You have two options when setting up per-domain languages:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Different domains</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If, for example, you have two domains ‚Äì<strong> example.com</strong> for your English language, and <strong>example.de</strong> for your German language, by using that option you can achieve that.<br />\n<strong>example.com &gt; English</strong><br />\n<strong>example.de &gt; German</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sub-domains</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can also use sub-domains- like in example: <strong>en.example.com</strong> ‚Äì for your English language and <strong>de.example.com</strong> for your German language.<br />\n<strong>en.example.com &gt; English</strong><br />\n<strong>de.example.com &gt; German</strong></p>\n<p>So, the next big question is how you can achieve that. The answer depends on two main components of your site‚Äôs setup:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your DNS server</li>\n<li>Your HTTP server (Apache, Nginx, etc.)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Setting up your DNS server</strong></h2>\n<h3><strong>Manual setup</strong></h3>\n<h4><strong>DNS settings with top level domains setup</strong></h4>\n<p>If you have different top level domains (<strong>example.com</strong>, <strong>example.de</strong>), you first need to configure them to have the proper authoritative DNS servers. This is usually done in the settings panel provided by the company that you bought your domain from.</p>\n<p>When you have added the domain, you need to create a record in your DNS server, that points to your HTTP server. Simply put, server needs to know what data to provide your users with, once they are on a specific domain. If they reach the <strong>.de</strong> domain, you want server to show them the German version of your site.</p>\n<p>If you have your own DNS server, you can (and it is best to) create an ‚Äú<strong>A Record</strong>‚Äù for your other domain that points to your server.</p>\n<p>There are two different records that you can use.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>A record</strong> ‚Äì you specify the IP of your server ‚Äì this is a good and fast solution</li>\n<li><strong>CNAME record</strong> ‚Äì you specify domain name for your server ‚Äì a little bit slow, but good if you change the server IP addresses often</li>\n</ul>\n<div id="attachment_860381" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/cname.vs_.a.png"><img class="wp-image-860381 size-medium" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/cname.vs_.a-300x75.png" alt="List of records. Your screens for configuring top level domains may differ." width="300" height="75" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/cname.vs_.a-300x75.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/cname.vs_.a-150x37.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/cname.vs_.a.png 499w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">List of records. Your screens for configuring top level domains may differ.</p></div>\n<h3><strong>DNS settings with sub-domains setup</strong></h3>\n<p>The setup for sub-domains is easy! You just create an additional <strong>A</strong> or <strong>CNAME</strong> record in your DNS server and point it to the same <strong>HTTP</strong>¬†/ <strong>HTTPS</strong> server IP or domain.</p>\n<div id="attachment_860378" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/a.record.png"><img class="wp-image-860378 size-medium" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/a.record-300x226.png" alt="Your screens for configuring subdomains may differ" width="300" height="226" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/a.record-300x226.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/a.record-150x113.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/a.record.png 526w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text">Your screens for configuring subdomains may differ</p></div>\n<p>Please note that after you complete this settings, you need to continue with the ‚Äú<strong>Setting up your HTTP server</strong>‚Äù part of this guide.</p>\n<h3>cPanel setup</h3>\n<p>Using Cpanel automatically adds the necessary DNS and HTTP entries, so you need to do only this in order to prepare your server.<br />\nSetting up top level domain<br />\nIn most cases the part of your cpanel that you need to use, looks like this.</p>\n<p><a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/domains.cpanel.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-860382 size-medium" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/domains.cpanel-300x65.png" alt="domains.cpanel" width="300" height="65" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/domains.cpanel-300x65.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/domains.cpanel-150x32.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/domains.cpanel.png 651w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a></p>\n<p>You can use two kind of methods to add your additional domain:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Parked domain</strong> ‚Äì to park the additional domain name ‚Äì this is the best option, since it uses the same path for your site in the http settings.<a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/parked.domain.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-860384 size-medium" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/parked.domain-300x245.png" alt="Parked domain screen" width="300" height="245" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/parked.domain-300x245.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/parked.domain-150x123.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/parked.domain-768x628.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/parked.domain.png 962w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a></li>\n<li><strong>Addon domain</strong> ‚Äì you must be careful to specify the folder with your current WordPress install<a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/add-on.domain.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-860379 size-medium" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/add-on.domain-298x300.png" alt="Add-on domain screen" width="298" height="300" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/add-on.domain-298x300.png 298w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/add-on.domain-150x150.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/add-on.domain-768x772.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/add-on.domain-90x90.png 90w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/add-on.domain.png 946w" sizes="(max-width: 298px) 100vw, 298px" /></a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Having done that, you can now go to ‚Äú<strong>Wrapping things up</strong>‚Äù part of this guide.<br />\nAll settings for your Apache and DNS will be created and added by Cpanel and everything should work.</p>\n<h4>Setting up the subdomains</h4>\n<p>To use a subdomain setup, you need to select the subdomains icon from the Cpanel menu.<br />\nWhen creating a subdomain you have to point it to where your WordPress has been installed before in order to work with ‚ÄúDifferent domain per language‚Äù option in WPML.<a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/subdomain.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-860385 size-medium" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/subdomain-300x152.png" alt="Subdomains screen" width="300" height="152" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/subdomain-300x152.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/subdomain-150x76.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/subdomain-768x388.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/subdomain.png 942w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a></p>\n<p>Having done that, you can now go to ‚Äú<strong>Wrapping things up</strong>‚Äù part of this guide.<br />\nAll settings for your Apache and DNS will be created and added by Cpanel and everything should work.</p>\n<p><strong>Make sure that all domains point to the same root WordPress folder after double-checking the configuration.</strong></p>\n<h2><strong>Setting up your HTTP server</strong></h2>\n<p>Okay, so we come to the second most important part of the setup, when you are using a server that you can manage.</p>\n<p>In order for your settings to work, you need to create an entry in your web server that will recognize the domain name (or the sub-domain name) that you have just added and pointed to in your <strong>DNS</strong> server.</p>\n<p>If you are running and administrating your own server, it is pretty easy ‚Äì you just need to add server alias to your current configuration.</p>\n<p>Following is an example used for the <strong>Apache</strong> server setup.</p>\n<pre class="brush: plain; title: ; notranslate">\n DocumentRoot &quot;/var/www/www.example.com/webroot&quot;\n  ServerName example.com\n  ServerAlias example.de\n...\n</pre>\n<p>That‚Äôs all to add &#8211; easy, right?<br />\nIt is similarly easy to setup this up on the <strong>Nginx</strong> server.</p>\n<pre class="brush: plain; title: ; notranslate">\n server {\n  server_name example.com example.de;\n...\n</pre>\n<p>Whichever route you choose, the most important thing to consider is that the alias configuration should all point to the same physical folder where your WordPress is being installed.</p>\n<h2><strong>Wrapping things up</strong></h2>\n<p>When you have all this set up you can change the settings on the<strong> WPML</strong> -&gt; <strong>Languages to Different domain per language</strong>. When you fill out the information required (the other domain or subdomain), pressing the Save button should validate your domain. It will report if there are any problems with the validation, and then save all the settings that you have made.</p>\n<h2><strong>Debugging</strong></h2>\n<p>If you still have problems with the new setup it is best to enable debugging in WordPress. You can do this by adding the following snippet to your WordPress site‚Äôs <strong>wp-config.php</strong> file.</p>\n<pre class="brush: plain; title: ; notranslate">\n// Turn debugging on\ndefine(''WP_DEBUG'', true);\n\n// Tell WordPress to log everything to /wp-content/debug.log\ndefine(''WP_DEBUG_LOG'', true);\n\n// Turn off the display of error messages on your site\ndefine(''WP_DEBUG_DISPLAY'', false);\n\n// For good measure, you can also add the follow code, which will hide errors from being displayed on-screen\n@ini_set(''display_errors'', 0);\n</pre>\n<p>Then you need to monitor the log file that will be created in <strong>/wp-content/debug.log</strong> when you save the domain options in WPML.</p>\n<p>You can also monitor the <strong>admin-ajax.php</strong> response in your browser console (press<strong> F12</strong> on your keyboard to show the console). Based on the console output and the log from ..<strong>/wp-content/debug.log</strong> &#8211; you can disable non vital WordPress plugins to try and find the source of the problem.<a href="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/browser.console.png"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-860380 size-medium" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/browser.console-300x211.png" alt="Browser console example" width="300" height="211" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/browser.console-300x211.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/browser.console-150x106.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/browser.console-768x541.png 768w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/browser.console-1024x721.png 1024w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/browser.console.png 1413w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a></p>\n<p>If you still have issues it is best to contact one of our specialists here in the WPML forums.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id="attachment_860449" style="width: 310px" class="wp-caption alignright"><img class="wp-image-860449 size-medium" src="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/picture-300x300.png" alt="George Botsev" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://d2salfytceyqoe.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/picture-300x300.png 300w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/picture-150x150.png 150w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/picture-90x90.png 90w, https://wpml.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/picture.png 480w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /><p class="wp-caption-text">George Botsev</p></div>\n<p style="text-align: left;">I am a geeky guy, that likes Star Trek, computers, and all other geeky stuff. My other interests are mainly related to IT, System Administration, Electronics, Open Source Software, Open Source Hardware, Photography, and Music.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">I have more than 10 years experience with WordPress, and also about 10 years professional experience with IT and System Administration.</p>\n<p style="text-align: left;">My main duty has always been to debug issues, and since September 2014, I joined the WPML Support team and I help some of you in the forums to resolve your problems.</p>\n<p style="text-align: right;">\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=Pv7Xg6vCv-s:68GcasIfnJ0:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=Pv7Xg6vCv-s:68GcasIfnJ0:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=Pv7Xg6vCv-s:68GcasIfnJ0:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=Pv7Xg6vCv-s:68GcasIfnJ0:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=Pv7Xg6vCv-s:68GcasIfnJ0:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=Pv7Xg6vCv-s:68GcasIfnJ0:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/Pv7Xg6vCv-s" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/use-wpml-different-domains-per-language/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/use-wpml-different-domains-per-language/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"Announcing WPML 3.3.8 beta";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:51:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/wpml/~3/wm3JNTzA7Uw/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"https://wpml.org/2016/04/announcing-wpml-3-3-8-beta/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 21 Apr 2016 07:55:58 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Announcements";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"WPML versions";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:26:"https://wpml.org/?p=863022";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:366:"We have recently released WPML 3.3.7 to address some changes introduced in WordPress 4.5. After this release, we noticed several issues with permalink handling, in particular with paginated content, and a couple of additional issues when dealing with WooCommerce. Some of these issues were already present in previous versions of WPML, but they became more [&#8230;]";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"Andrea";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3894:"<p>We have recently released WPML 3.3.7 to address some changes introduced in WordPress 4.5.</p>\n<p>After this release, we noticed several issues with permalink handling, in particular with paginated content, and a couple of additional issues when dealing with WooCommerce.</p>\n<p>Some of these issues were already present in previous versions of WPML, but they became more evident in WPML 3.3.7.</p>\n<p>WPML 3.3.8 addresses these issues, and in particular:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Templates and pagination\n<ul>\n<li>Wrong template being used in the search results for a second language when the front page has a template and there is no template for the search results</li>\n<li>is_front_page() does not work when the URL contains the &#8220;lang&#8221; argument in addition to others arguments</li>\n<li>Pagination issues in the default language with browser redirect enabled</li>\n<li>Malformed paginated URL in the home page with plain permalinks and language as a parameter</li>\n<li>Wrong pagination when using custom permalinks such as &#8220;/%postname%&#8221; without a trailing slash, and language as a parameter</li>\n<li>Malformed pagination URL when displaying paginated content on the front page with &#8220;Post name<!-- Do you mean /%postname% here, as in the previous bullet point? -->&#8221; permalinks and language as a parameter</li>\n<li>The second page of paginated content is not accessible in a secondary language with pretty permalinks and the same slug in translated content</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>WooCommerce related\n<ul>\n<li>301 error on product pages</li>\n<li>Different domains for each language; when switching language, the cart contents are not synchronized</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Others\n<ul>\n<li>PHP Notice: Undefined offset: 0 in sitepress.class.php on line 2345</li>\n<li>‚ÄúLanguage as parameter‚Äù<!-- Do you mean ‚ÄòLanguage-as-parameter conflicts‚Äô here? --> conflicts with browser redirection<!-- Do you mean ‚Äòbrowser redirection‚Äô here? --> and the manually set home page</li>\n<li>Added ability to change the behavior of the ‚Äúheads_lang‚Äù meta tags by providing new hooks</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Some of the above issues were discovered thanks to a new set of automated tests that we added specifically for this release.</p>\n<h2>Download and give us feedback</h2>\n<p>First, remember to backup your site before updating. We backup our site and test updates before we update ANYTHING (any plugin, the theme or WordPress). This release of WPML has gone through a lot of testing, but it‚Äôs still nicer to find glitches on a test site and not on a production server.</p>\n<p>Then, update all of WPML components. This is a quick fix version of WPML core and WPML Translation Management, with no dependencies between other add-ons, which in fact haven&#8217;t been updated.</p>\n<p>The best way to update WPML is from the WordPress admin. Register your site (you can register all your sites, we don‚Äôt limit) to get automated updates. Alternatively, you can always download WPML manually from <a href="https://wpml.org/account/">your account</a>.</p>\n<p>Leave your comments to give us your feedback, ask questions or make suggestions. We‚Äôll get back to you.</p>\n<h2></h2>\n<div class="feedflare">\n<a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=wm3JNTzA7Uw:FUqumHwl9Yk:D7DqB2pKExk"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=wm3JNTzA7Uw:FUqumHwl9Yk:D7DqB2pKExk" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=wm3JNTzA7Uw:FUqumHwl9Yk:gIN9vFwOqvQ"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=wm3JNTzA7Uw:FUqumHwl9Yk:gIN9vFwOqvQ" border="0"></img></a> <a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?a=wm3JNTzA7Uw:FUqumHwl9Yk:V_sGLiPBpWU"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/wpml?i=wm3JNTzA7Uw:FUqumHwl9Yk:V_sGLiPBpWU" border="0"></img></a>\n</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/wpml/~4/wm3JNTzA7Uw" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"https://wpml.org/20