(2907, 402, 'gallery_0_text', 'Paris, September 30, 2015\r\n\r\n<i>Download PDF version <a href="http://yxelia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Communiqu√©-Yxelia-VUK.pdf">here</a>.</i>\r\n\r\nLAUNCH BY YXELIA OF NEW SUBSIDIARY SETELIA DIGITAL\r\n\r\nYXELIA management is pleased to announce today the signing of an agreement to launch a new subsidiary in France called SETELIA Digital, and directed by Louis-Marie GUILLAUME, specializing in:\r\n- The migration of business processes towards digital architectures, including the issues of security and mobility.\r\n- Connected objects\r\n\r\nLouis-Marie GUILLAUME started his career in 1990 as Business Engineer at Dun & Bradstreet Software, then in 1996 as Sales and Marketing Director of Matranet, and in 1999 he became Managing Director of the subsidiary France Broadvision software, provider for the web. He joined Vignette in 2002 in the publishing of web content. After six years at Oracle in commercial management positions, he was appointed CEO of Airweb, a German-French company expert in mobile solutions.\r\n\r\n"It is a great honor to join a fast-growing project like YXELIA and to benefit of the widely recognized international expertise of SETELIA in the telecom sector. SETELIA Digital has the means to support its customers in their digital development by providing secure solutions, innovative and attractive. " declared Louis-Marie GUILLAUME.\r\n\r\n"With over 10 years of successful experience in the certification and integration of innovative technology solutions for all Telecom Operators in France and abroad, we intend to offer our expertise in Telecom environments to other sectors of activity in a broader sense with SETELIA Digital and are happy to associate Louis-Marie Guillaume to our plans "explained Malek OUADI, COO of SETELIA on this occasion.\r\n\r\nThis is the fourth operation of the Group that was launched in October 2014, after the acquisition of SETELIA Group, the launch of the subsidiary SETELIA Benelux in Belgium in January 2015 and the acquisition of AVANCE group in Holland in May 2015.\r\n\r\nAbout Yxelia\r\nEstablished in October 2014, the Group Yxelia represents a workforce of over 350 consultants for a turnover of ‚Ç¨30 million, split between France, Belgium, Holland and Lebanon. Basing its strategy on organic growth and a policy of dynamic external growth, Yxelia Group aims at becoming a major international player in the world of Network & Telecom.\r\n\r\nContacts:\r\nYxelia ‚Äê Carlos BEDRAN - +33 (0) 1 55 43 26 00 / email: carlos@yxelia.com\r\nSetelia ‚Äê Louis-Marie GUILLAUME ‚Äê +33 (0) 1 55 43 26 00 / email: louis‚Äêmarie.guillaume@setelia.com'),
